<% content_for :title, "API Documentation — SPARC" %>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">

    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4">
      <div>
        <h1 class="h2 fw-bold">API Documentation</h1>
        <p class="text-body-secondary mb-0">SPARC REST API v1 &mdash; all endpoints require Bearer token authentication</p>
      </div>
      <%= link_to "&larr; About".html_safe, about_path, class: "btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" %>
    </div>

    <hr>

    <%# ── Slug / ID Lookup ── %>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--sparc-primary);">Resource Identifiers: <code>:slug</code> vs <code>:id</code></h2>
      <p>
        SPARC uses two types of resource identifiers in API paths:
      </p>
      <div class="table-responsive">
        <table class="table table-bordered">
          <thead><tr><th style="width: 20%;">Identifier</th><th style="width: 35%;">Format</th><th>Used By</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>:slug</code></td>
              <td>URL-friendly string, e.g. <code>acme-cloud-ssp-rev5</code></td>
              <td>SSP, SAR, SAP, POA&amp;M, Profile, and CDEF documents</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>:id</code></td>
              <td>Numeric database ID, e.g. <code>42</code></td>
              <td>Control Catalogs, Control Mappings, Users, Authorization Boundaries, KSI resources</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-body-secondary">
        Slugs are auto-generated from the document title when created. You can find a resource's slug in the
        <code>slug</code> field returned by any list or show endpoint. Use the slug (not the numeric ID) when
        calling document endpoints.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%# ── Authentication ── %>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--sparc-primary);">Authentication</h2>
      <p>All API requests require a Bearer token in the <code>Authorization</code> header:</p>
      <pre class="p-3 rounded" style="background: var(--sparc-surface-alt); overflow-x: auto;"><code>Authorization: Bearer sparc_your_token_here</code></pre>

      <h5 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">Authentication Modes</h5>
      <p>
        SPARC supports three API authentication modes, controlled by the
        <code>SPARC_API_AUTH</code> environment variable:
      </p>
      <div class="table-responsive">
        <table class="table table-bordered">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Mode</th>
              <th><code>SPARC_API_AUTH</code></th>
              <th>Token Source</th>
              <th>Best For</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Local</strong></td>
              <td><code>local</code> (default)</td>
              <td>API tokens generated via Rails console or service accounts</td>
              <td>Development, standalone deployments</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>OIDC</strong></td>
              <td><code>oidc</code></td>
              <td>OIDC access tokens issued by an identity provider (e.g., Okta)</td>
              <td>SSO-only environments with centralized identity</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Hybrid</strong></td>
              <td><code>hybrid</code></td>
              <td>Both local API tokens and OIDC tokens accepted</td>
              <td>Production deployments needing both pipeline tokens and SSO</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h5 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">Service Accounts &amp; Pipeline Tokens</h5>
      <p>
        For CI/CD pipelines and automated integrations, create <strong>service accounts</strong>
        with scoped API tokens. Service account tokens work in <code>local</code> and
        <code>hybrid</code> modes and are ideal for non-interactive workflows where OIDC
        tokens are not practical.
      </p>
      <p>
        Generate tokens via the Rails console:
      </p>
      <pre class="p-3 rounded" style="background: var(--sparc-surface-alt); overflow-x: auto;"><code>token = ApiToken.generate!(user: User.find_by(email: "admin@sparc.local"), name: "My API Token")
puts token.plaintext_token  # Save this &mdash; cannot be retrieved again</code></pre>
      <p class="small text-body-secondary">
        Tokens are SHA-256 digested before storage. The plaintext is only available at creation time.
        In <code>oidc</code> mode, local tokens are rejected &mdash; use OIDC access tokens instead.
        In <code>hybrid</code> mode, SPARC tries local token lookup first, then falls back to OIDC validation.
      </p>
      <p class="small text-body-secondary">
        Responses use standard HTTP status codes: 200 (success), 201 (created), 401 (unauthorized),
        403 (forbidden), 404 (not found), 422 (validation error).
      </p>
    </section>

    <%# ── Response Format ── %>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--sparc-primary);">Response Format</h2>
      <p>All list endpoints return paginated responses with this structure:</p>
      <pre class="p-3 rounded" style="background: var(--sparc-surface-alt); overflow-x: auto;"><code>{
  "data": [ ... ],
  "meta": {
    "current_page": 1,
    "total_pages": 5,
    "total_count": 48,
    "per_page": 10
  }
}</code></pre>
      <p>Use <code>?page=2</code> and <code>?per_page=25</code> query parameters for pagination.</p>
    </section>

    <%# ── Discovery ── %>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--sparc-primary);">API Discovery</h2>
      <p>The discovery endpoint returns a list of all available API endpoints scoped to the caller's authorization. Use it to verify connectivity, discover capabilities, and detect permission changes.</p>
      <div class="table-responsive">
        <table class="table table-bordered">
          <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th><th>Permission</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="badge bg-primary">GET</span></td><td><code>/api/v1/available</code></td><td>Returns endpoint inventory scoped to caller permissions</td><td>Any authenticated user</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <h5 class="fw-bold mt-3 mb-2">Response Example</h5>
      <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded"><code>{
  "api_version": "v1",
  "system_id": "sparc-application",
  "authenticated_as": "sparc-iac Pipeline",
  "auth_mode": "hybrid",
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "path": "/api/v1/ssp_documents",
      "methods": ["GET", "POST"],
      "description": "System Security Plans"
    },
    {
      "path": "/api/v1/ssp_documents/:slug",
      "methods": ["GET"],
      "description": "Single SSP document"
    }
  ]
}</code></pre>
      <p class="text-muted mt-2"><strong>Authorization scoping:</strong> Admins see all endpoints and methods. Non-admins see only the resources and HTTP methods their role permits. Read-only users see only GET methods. Endpoints with no permitted methods are omitted entirely.</p>
    </section>

